* do not add a timeout fallback in v1. Dispatch is the spine of the recent-activity section; falling back to git-only narrative on a slow run would silently degrade the headline output. If real-world usage shows dispatch consistently exceeding ~30s, revisit then with concrete numbers rather than speculation.\n- **Repo without recent agent activity.** A brand-new or low-activity repo will produce a thin narrative section. The plan handles this explicitly, but we should verify the tone reads helpful rather than broken.\n- **Focused search-term quality.** Seeding `entire search` from repo name, top-level directories, and dispatch nouns is more robust than an empty query, but weak term selection could still miss important threads. Mitigation: cap to a small batch, then dedupe and fall back to git-only hot files when the checkpoint corpus stays sparse.\n- **Skill name collision.** `project-overview` is descriptive but generic. **Resolved:** ship as `project-overview`. Verify during PR by running the skill alongside the existing four (`session-handoff`, `explain`, `what-happened`, `search`) in each install path documented in `README.md`; rename to `entire-project-overview` only if a real collision is observed.\n\n## Decision\n\nReady for quorum.\n\n---\n\nBegin.\n"}}
